theorem Topology.dense_iff_interior_compl_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- First direction: a dense set has complement with empty interior.
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    have hClosure : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
    -- `interior (Aᶜ)` is contained in the (empty) complement of `closure A`.
    have hSub :
        interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ⊆ (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
      intro x hxInt
      -- Suppose `x ∈ closure A`; derive a contradiction.
      have hxInt' := hxInt
      by
        intro hxClos
        rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hxInt' with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_sub⟩
        have hUE : ((U : Set X) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
          (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClos U hU_open hxU
        rcases hUE with ⟨y, hyU, hyA⟩
        have : (y : X) ∈ ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := hU_sub hyU
        exact this hyA
    -- Since `(closure A)ᶜ = ∅`, the interior is empty.
    have : interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ⊆ (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [hClosure] using
        (show interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ⊆ ((Set.univ : Set X))ᶜ from by
          simpa [hClosure] using hSub)
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm this (Set.empty_subset _)
  -- Second direction: empty interior of the complement implies density.
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- Points outside `closure A` are interior points of `Aᶜ`.
    have hCompSub :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := by
      intro x hxComp
      have hOpen : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
        isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
      have hSub : ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
        intro y hy
        intro hyA
        exact hy (subset_closure hyA)
      -- `x` is in the interior via the open set `(closure A)ᶜ`.
      exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 ⟨_, hOpen, hxComp, hSub⟩
    -- Hence `(closure A)ᶜ` is empty, so `closure A = univ`.
    have hComplEmpty :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm
      ·
        have : ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
          hCompSub
        simpa [hIntEmpty] using this
      · exact Set.empty_subset _
    have hClosureUniv : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      have hCompl : Set.compl (closure (A : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa using hComplEmpty
      simpa using congrArg Set.compl hCompl
    exact (dense_iff_closure_eq).2 hClosureUniv

theorem Topology.dense_iff_interior_compl_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- A convenient rewrite of `interior (Aᶜ)`.
  have hIntCompl : interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) := by
    simpa using interior_compl (A := A)
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    -- For a dense set, its closure is the whole space.
    have hClosure : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
    -- Rewrite and simplify.
    have : interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) := hIntCompl
    simpa [hClosure] using this
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- `interior (Aᶜ) = ∅` implies `(closure A)ᶜ = ∅`.
    have hComplEmpty : ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      have : interior (Aᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := hIntEmpty
      simpa [hIntCompl] using this
    -- Hence `closure A = univ`.
    have hClosureUniv : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      have hEq : closure (A : Set X) = Set.compl ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) := by
        ext x; simp
      simpa [hComplEmpty, Set.compl_empty] using hEq
    -- Conclude density.
    exact (dense_iff_closure_eq).2 hClosureUniv

theorem Topology.interior_inter_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ interior A ∩ interior B := by
  intro x hx
  -- `A ∩ B` is contained in `A`, hence their interiors satisfy the same relation.
  have hA : (x : X) ∈ interior A := by
    have h_subset : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  -- Similarly, `A ∩ B` is contained in `B`.
  have hB : (x : X) ∈ interior B := by
    have h_subset : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.2
    exact (interior_mono h_subset) hx
  exact And.intro hA hB
